@endnode

@node "Playing..." "Playing..."
 PLAYING

    When you start Atoms3.1, you can see the Preferences screen: you can
select the four player among:
   1- Human: you are the player and you put atoms with the mouse pointer.
   2- None: The player is out.
   3- Computer Easy: The computer will play in an easy way.
   4- Computer Hard: It's a more difficult level!! You can also select if
you want the music during the game or not and if you want to see the
electrons moving aroud the atoms.
    Every time the preferences are saved in s: directory (if available), so
you will not have to re-enter them every time you play Atoms3.1 (I hope
often!!).


    Then click start and you're on the board game!

     It is very easy to play: each player puts in the table an atom and
adding them in the same place it will explodes. In the corners they explode
when they are just 2, on the sides when they are 3 and elsewhere when 4. You
can start a non-stop reaction and so win.... Don't worry if it seems you're
losing: a player can win even with just an atom!!

     Press "m" to switch the music on/off.
     Press "e" to stop/restart the moviment of electrons.
     Press Esc to quit the game.

     A tip? Don't put your atoms to close one another because you could lose
them all together, and use diagonals as much as possible.
@endnode

